@Node "Fut" "Future"

  @{b}Future:@{ub}

    Dunno. 
    There is obviously room for improvements, but is it worth it..

    Minor changes might be to have the input scripts loop, rather
    than exit after every character, or do away with the string requesters
    altogether, by taking the strings directly off the page - something
    that would require rexxtricks.library or equivalent, for clipboard
    access.

    One could have Pagestream open a separate document, to display more
    than one character for selection at a time, in an organised manner.
    I kind of like the current approach though.

    Maybe a popup button bar with commonly used characters would 
    be something. Done the right way, you could perhaps enter entire
    sentences with a few mouse klicks. RxMUI should be able to do it,
    although it would require quite a nasty bit of manual labour and
    figuring out how to group characters for best effect...

@EndNode
